			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't think any NES emulator accurately emulates what can happen when writing to the PPU in an active scanline. An easy 'fix' for your program is: vblank NMI -&gt; disable PPU -&gt; upload data to PPU -&gt; enable PPU.
<br />
<br />Also, be sure to do a sprite DMA every vblank, as sprite attribute RAM contents may deteriorate if untouched for a while (not sure of this myself). This effect is also not emulated.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
